5:
This is the Cradle? It feels so cold... 
and lonely.
16:
Oh, how predictable. I knew you'd 
come looking for the World Flipper. 
Like mice after cheese.
19:
Administrator... So you were really 
here...
23:
But on this planet, no one does 
anything... without my permission.
28:
Argh... What are these bars MADE 
of?
Dia, get out of here NOW!
32:
Welcome back, Diva my sweet. Now 
what say we wash out that cute little 
brain of yours?
44:
You can erase my memories. You can 
make me your perfect canary. I'll sing 
for you and never even think of flying 
away...
47:
So please... Just let them go! Send 
them home!
51:
Oh, Diva. I'd no doubt you'd come 
around in the end!
54:
Dia, no... You can't do this... This is 
not... what you want...
57: But it is. I want to save you guys.
59:
And, well... somewhere in my heart, 
I knew. I could never make it in a new 
world. I'm just not strong enough.
65:
The only thing I can do is sing... I just 
sing fake songs with a fake voice that 
can be replicated a hundred times 
over!
67:
And, you know, I would never have 
become a singer if it weren't for Regis. 
It's fine, okay? I belong here!
75:
Dia... I love your music. So come with 
us. Please!
79:
I want to... I really want to. But my 
music can't save you!
97:
Oh, Alpha, Beta... I'm sorry, but that's 
the only song I know.
100:
Whaaat? Why? I thought humans 
knew tons of songs.
102:
And you thought right, little one. We 
humans were always singing.
103:
But... Oh, how do I put this? Human 
memories are VERY complex. There 
was far too much data between us to 
contain in one machine... but one 
machine is all we had.
105:
To compact "us" into "me," some 
memories had to be cut. For example, 
I remember a little girl who brought 
our shelter hope with her singing but... 
*sigh* Her songs elude me.
110:
There used to be lots of different 
humans, right, Admin?
116:
Beta, why would you say that? I have 
you, don't I?
120:
Oh yeaaah. So I guess you're not 
lonely, huh?
128:
You liar. You're actually super lonely. 
I can tell.
131: But I know how to make it all better!
141:
Alpha... Where did you learn that 
song?
145:
I just knew it. We can remember things 
you forgot, you know.
148: Cause we're a part of you!
159: Get your filthy grippers OFF MY DIVA!
168: Vile, vulgar junk! I'll ERASE you!
177: Your very existence is a transgression!
191: Tin man? The hell are you doing?
194:
Why, I'm leading the charge! Now, 
come on, chums! Have at her!
197:
I meant, what makes you think you 
can come strutting back—
AGH! I'll get to you later!
204:
Oh, Dia... I know I have a lot of 
explaining to do, but let me just say 
this for now.
206:
Go wherever your heart desires. You 
aren't the type of royalty that can be 
kept in a tower.
...Isn't that right, my headstrong 
princess?
